{
  "texts": [
    "Section 7: Future directions and opportunities for enhancing orthopedic education with generative AIThe future of orthopedic education with generative AI holds promising opportunities.",
    "Advancements in AI technology can lead to development of more accurate and reliable educational tools, minimizing the risks of misinformation and bias.",
    "Transparency, responsibility, and rigorous assessment of AI systems are all aspects that must be explored and enhanced to assure the trustworthiness and quality of the outcomes [158].",
    "AI can utilize ML algorithms trained on large datasets to evaluate source trustworthiness using source consistency and reputation analysis, with the aim of identifying probable patterns of disinformation or the spread of incorrect information [159].To overcome generative AI's current limitations in generating extensive orthopedic knowledge and responding to complex questions, the authors suggest that specific training and access to orthopedic literature could allow generative AI to perform better and even excel over orthopedic exams.",
    "Integrating AI with real-time data updates will ensure that the knowledge base remains current and relevant."
  ]
}